transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at Score Blue.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Yes, I need to cancel my order.

Speaker 2: I don't know why you took the money out automatically.

Speaker 1: Because I thought I canceled it last month,

Speaker 2: but I tried it out and it don't work for me.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir.

Speaker 2: Let me pull up your prescription here

Speaker 1: and let's see what's going on.

Speaker 2: Could I get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: Stanley Jenkins, April the 22nd, 1960.

Speaker 2: Okay, Stanley, I see the prescription was for

Speaker 1: the 50 milligram Viagra AGB, is that accurate?

Speaker 2: Or is it written December 23rd?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, it looks like the doctor wrote it with refills

Speaker 1: and that was due to the low milligram dosage.

Speaker 2: So Stanley, yeah, you're not required

Speaker 1: to get this every month.

Speaker 2: It just appears that's how the doctor wrote it initially.

Speaker 1: It does come with a total of 12 refills altogether.

Speaker 2: This is not a subscription, this is a prescription.

Speaker 1: So if you wanted, you could simply pause it

Speaker 2: and then you could call in and place refill

Speaker 1: orders as needed.

Speaker 2: No, I want to cancel, it don't work for me.

Speaker 1: I want my money refunded.

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, so if you want a refund,

Speaker 1: I just need you to put return to sender

Speaker 2: on that package and get it back to us.

Speaker 1: Oh, you send it already?

Speaker 2: Well, it appears here that it has been shipped.

Speaker 1: It does have a tracking number.

Speaker 2: I went through on the 23rd for that refill.

Speaker 1: Okay, so when I get it returned.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir, exactly.

Speaker 1: Okay, now my question to you, sir,

Speaker 2: did you try to take two of them?

Speaker 1: Did you attempt 100 milligrams?

Speaker 2: I took two of them.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I took two and still didn't work.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I told you I don't do it by, I do see how it works.

Speaker 2: It doesn't value, but when it come in, I will return it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, I went ahead and canceled that prescription.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
